Master Explorer			KEY:Pathfinder Delver ~ Master Explorer			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary			DEFINE:PaDSkillBonus|0																					DESC:You add %1 to all Disable Device and Perception checks. You can disable traps in half the normal amount of time (minimum 1 round) and open a lock as a standard action. You can always take 10 on Disable Device and Stealth checks. You can use Disable Device to disarm magical traps.|PaDSkillBonus																																																																																																																																																												BONUS:SKILL|Disable Device,Perception|PaDSkillBonus																										SOURCEPAGE:p.58
Surefooted				KEY:Pathfinder Delver ~ Surefooted				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																											DESC:You can move through difficult terrain at your normal speed. Ground that has been magically manipulated to impeded motion still affects you normally.																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.58
Thrilling Escape			KEY:Pathfinder Delver ~ Thrilling Escape			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary			DEFINE:PaDEscapeTimes|0																					DESC:You can attempt to delay a trap immediately after triggering it. You make a Disable Device check as an immediate action against the trap's Disable Device DC; if you are successful, the trap's activation is delayed until the end of your next turn. You can attempt this check even if the trap was triggered by a failed Disable Device check, or if it is not your turn. You can do this %1/day.|PaDEscapeTimes																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.58
Guardbreaker			KEY:Pathfinder Delver ~ Guardbreaker			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																											DESC:Your familiarity with the strange guardians often left in tombs allows you to attack them more effectively. You may treat your trap sense bonus as if it were a favored enemy bonus against constructs, oozes, and undead.																																																																																			ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|PaDFE Construct|!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Favored Enemy (Construct)	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|PaDFE Ooze|!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Favored Enemy (Ooze)	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|PaDFE Undead|!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Favored Enemy (Undead)																																										BONUS:VAR|FavoredConstruct,FavoredOoze,FavoredUndead|TrapSenseBonus										SOURCEPAGE:p.58
Resourceful Disabler		KEY:Pathfinder Delver ~ Resourceful Disabler		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																											DESC:You are adept at making use of what's at hand. You can use the Disable Device skill without tools at no penalty.																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.58
Vigilant Combatant		KEY:Pathfinder Delver ~ Vigilant Combatant		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary			DEFINE:PaDInitiative|0																					DESC:You add %1 to initiative checks.|PaDInitiative																																																																																																																																																																																			BONUS:COMBAT|Initiative|PaDInitiative																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.58
Left for Dead			KEY:Pathfinder Delver ~ Left for Dead			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural																											DESC:1/day, you can cheat death. If you would be killed by a melee attack, ranged attack, or an effect that requires a saving throw, you are instead reduced to -1 hit points and knocked unconscious, but are stable. You appear dead, but become conscious 1 minute later unless awakened sooner.																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.58
Fortunate Soul			KEY:Pathfinder Delver ~ Fortunate Soul			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural			DEFINE:PaDFortunateTimes|0																				DESC:You may reroll any saving throw you have just made before the results of the roll are revealed. You must take the result of the reroll, even if it's worse than the original roll. You may use this ability %1/day.|PaDFortunateTimes																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.58
True Seeing				KEY:Pathfinder Delver ~ True Seeing				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.SpellLike												SPELLS:Pathfinder Delver|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=PaDLvl|True Seeing,16+max(INT,WIS,CHA)			DESC:You can use true seeing 1/day (caster level %1).|PaDTrueSeeingLvl																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.58
Nick of Time			KEY:Pathfinder Delver ~ Nick of Time			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																											DESC:You have a knack for choosing the best time to act. 1/day, you can use an immediate action to perform an action that normally requires a standard action to perform.																																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.58

