#BLOCK: Student of War Special Abilities
Know Your Enemy			KEY:Student of War ~ Know Your Enemy			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary			DEFINE:SoWKnowEnemy|0	DEFINE:SoWDuration|0																	DESC:As a move action, you may study a foe that you can see and make a Knowledge check appropriate to the creature's type (DC10+HD). Success grants you a bonus against your enemy based on your stance for %1 mins or until you use the ability on another target. You may change your stance as a move action.|SoWDuration|PREVARLT:SoWLvl,7	DESC:As a swift action, you may study a foe that you can see and make a Knowledge check appropriate to the creature's type (DC10+HD). Success grants you a bonus against your enemy based on your stance for %1 mins or until you use the ability on another target. You may change your stance as a swift action.|SoWDuration|PREVARGTEQ:SoWLvl,7																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Mind Over Metal			KEY:Student of War ~ Mind Over Metal			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																											DESC:You are skilled at taking blows such that your armor or shield deflect them harmlessly. When using armor or shield, you can use your Intelligence modifier in place of your Dexterity modifier for determining your Armor Class.																																																																																																																																																					BONUS:COMBAT|AC|INT-DEX|TYPE=Ability.STACK|PREMULT:2,[PREEQUIP:1,TYPE=Armor,TYPE=Shield],[PREVARGT:INT,DEX]																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Anticipate				KEY:Student of War ~ Anticipate				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary			DEFINE:SoWAnticipateTimes|0																				DESC:You can anticipate your enemy's moves. %1/day as an immediate action, you can ignore any damage and effects of a spell or ability you successfully saved against. This ability has no effect against effects that do not allow saving throws.|SoWAnticipateTimes																																																																																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Telling Blow			KEY:Student of War ~ Telling Blow				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																											DESC:You can aim your blows at the weakest point in a studied foe's defense, ignoring up to 3 points of damage reduction. This does not apply to damage reduction without a type, and cannot be used against creatures that are immune to critical hits or otherwise lack discernible weak points.																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Nemesis				KEY:Student of War ~ Nemesis					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural																											DESC:You can focus upon a held weapon 1/day as a swift action, rendering it anathema to your studied creature. The weapon gains the bane property against the creature for 1 minute, or until you use know your enemy against a different foe.																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Deadly Blow				KEY:Student of War ~ Deadly Blow				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Supernatural																											DESC:Your awareness of your studied foe allows you to find weak spots where none should exist. If you use your know the enemy ability and beat the Knowledge check DC by 10 or more, you may ignore the target's natural damage reduction and immunity to critical hits and sneak attacks. This does not apply to immunities granted by spells, environmental effects, or equipment.																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.62

